1
00:00:04,704 --> 00:00:08,307
<i>In 2026, I, Kosei Neo,</i>

2
00:00:08,308 --> 00:00:09,609
<i>president of NEOXIS,</i>

3
00:00:10,176 --> 00:00:14,147
<i>should have died when someone pushed me…</i>

4
00:00:14,814 --> 00:00:16,081
<i>Yet somehow,</i>

5
00:00:16,082 --> 00:00:19,518
<i>I ended up in the body of Eito Nomoto,
who looked just like me</i>

6
00:00:19,519 --> 00:00:23,322
<i>and was supposed to have died
in an accident in 2012.</i>

7
00:00:23,323 --> 00:00:26,258
<i>He was the son of Eiji Nomoto,
the man caught in my fall.</i>

8
00:00:26,259 --> 00:00:27,226
SANYOKAN BUILDING

9
00:00:27,227 --> 00:00:30,230
<i>I will find whoever killed me.</i>

10
00:00:31,097 --> 00:00:34,600
<i>I revived the shopping street
I once forced into eviction</i>

11
00:00:34,601 --> 00:00:36,636
<i>and guided Sarasa,
whom Eito had proposed to,</i>

12
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:39,471
<i>toward a life as a painter.</i>

13
00:00:39,472 --> 00:00:40,572
A VISIONARY ARTIST
SARASA IKETANI

14
00:00:40,573 --> 00:00:43,175
We arrive in Paris on November 13th

15
00:00:43,176 --> 00:00:45,210
and stay for three days.

16
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:48,147
<i>November 13th…</i>

17
00:00:48,148 --> 00:00:50,416
<i>Isn't that the day of the Paris attacks?</i>

18
00:00:50,417 --> 00:00:54,420
<i>My actions as Eito have had an impact</i>

19
00:00:54,421 --> 00:00:57,357
<i>and changed the history of Kosei Neo.</i>

20
00:00:57,924 --> 00:01:01,895
<i>If Kosei Neo dies, what will happen to me?</i>

21
00:01:02,862 --> 00:01:04,130
<i>This is bad.</i>

22
00:01:04,631 --> 00:01:07,500
<i>This situation is incredibly bad.</i>

23
00:01:39,332 --> 00:01:41,101
Togo, what's the matter?

24
00:01:41,968 --> 00:01:45,304
President Nagamine was called

25
00:01:45,305 --> 00:01:47,507
to Tokyo by the chairman of Keidanren.

26
00:01:48,141 --> 00:01:51,311
He'd like to meet
in Tokyo instead of Paris.

27
00:01:52,245 --> 00:01:54,247
Such a sudden change of plans?

28
00:01:54,981 --> 00:01:59,952
Today, a discussion with Keidanren
and other events are scheduled.

29
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:04,624
President Nagamine would like to meet
tomorrow at Neo's company.

30
00:02:06,693 --> 00:02:08,027
Understood.

31
00:02:22,509 --> 00:02:23,709
Hello?

32
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:28,948
I did as you said.
So the deal will come together, yes?

33
00:02:33,052 --> 00:02:36,855
Things will definitely go better
than if they'd met in Paris.

34
00:02:36,856 --> 00:02:37,756
ISLAMIC EXTREMISTS
COORDINATED TERRORIST ATTACKS

35
00:02:37,757 --> 00:02:39,858
<i>On the night of the 13th local time,</i>

36
00:02:39,859 --> 00:02:43,195
<i>coordinated terrorist attacks
in Paris attributed to Islamic extremists</i>

37
00:02:43,196 --> 00:02:46,765
<i>left many dead and wounded.</i>

38
00:02:46,766 --> 00:02:48,534
<i>The death toll at the theater</i>

39
00:02:48,535 --> 00:02:51,637
<i>is believed to exceed 100.</i>

40
00:02:51,638 --> 00:02:54,140
I can't believe this happened in Paris…

41
00:02:54,807 --> 00:02:58,244
We would have been
at that theater ourselves…

42
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:02,648
I owe this to Togo, don't I?

43
00:03:02,649 --> 00:03:04,083
Togo?

44
00:03:05,418 --> 00:03:10,323
You were so insistent
that I come to Tokyo.

45
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:13,526
I…

46
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:16,595
simply passed along the wishes

47
00:03:16,596 --> 00:03:21,033
of the chairman of Keidanren
to meet with you.

48
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:24,837
Even so, it saved us…

49
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:29,142
Call it fate…

50
00:03:30,443 --> 00:03:33,078
A twist of destiny?

51
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:36,615
On that note, we'd be grateful

52
00:03:36,616 --> 00:03:39,551
if you'd consider NEOXIS as a partner

53
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:44,590
for Kumamoto Industry's
semiconductor business.

54
00:03:44,591 --> 00:03:48,761
Of course.
I'll give it serious consideration.

55
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:57,237
Now, what did you need from me?

56
00:03:58,171 --> 00:04:03,376
President Neo and I both have something
we can't quite make sense of.

57
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:08,513
Knowing we were heading to Paris,

58
00:04:08,514 --> 00:04:10,415
you brought President Nagamine to Tokyo.

59
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:12,151
You also didn't tell us.

60
00:04:14,153 --> 00:04:17,457
I wasn't sure he'd come
until the last moment.

61
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:21,894
And explaining why felt too delicate.

62
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:24,797
Too delicate, meaning what?

63
00:04:25,698 --> 00:04:28,101
That Tokyo was better for the deal.

64
00:04:29,502 --> 00:04:31,304
It was one man's hunch.

65
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:35,608
A hunch?

66
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:40,280
As a result,
you avoided the terror attacks,

67
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:45,051
and President Nagamine
warmed up to NEOXIS.

68
00:04:46,586 --> 00:04:50,923
But why would you act
on something so dubious?

69
00:04:51,424 --> 00:04:54,426
Before the Sochi Olympics,

70
00:04:54,427 --> 00:04:57,829
I was asked to produce
an ad with a figure skater.

71
00:04:57,830 --> 00:05:01,433
When I was unsure who to pick,

72
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:04,403
this man suggested Yuzuru Hanyu.

73
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:06,472
He guided me to success.

74
00:05:08,374 --> 00:05:11,611
He may have the ability
to foresee the future.

75
00:05:13,746 --> 00:05:15,381
What kind of man is he?

76
00:05:16,516 --> 00:05:18,484
He's like someone you know well.

77
00:05:21,554 --> 00:05:26,292
A man… who looks just like Kosei Neo.

78
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:30,730
Eri's brother, Eito Nomoto?!

79
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:34,433
He protected Akari Shopping Street
from Super Soman.

80
00:05:34,434 --> 00:05:35,033
GLOBAL WARMING COUNTERMEASURES FAIR

81
00:05:35,034 --> 00:05:37,437
<i>He even rattled Ichimanda.</i>

82
00:05:38,104 --> 00:05:39,972
Quite a remarkable man.

83
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:44,610
Akari Shopping Street is
tough competition.

84
00:05:45,111 --> 00:05:46,712
Their climate goods

85
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:49,716
are selling well online
through NEOXIS too.

86
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:53,985
NEOXIS and Akari Shopping Street
are working together?

87
00:05:53,986 --> 00:05:54,821
Yes!

88
00:05:56,255 --> 00:05:58,491
NEOXIS & AKARI SHOPPING STREET
COLLAB PRODUCT

89
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:07,399
Lotus root stuffed with mustard miso,
Sweet potato rice cake

90
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,400
horse meat sashimi!

91
00:06:08,401 --> 00:06:10,702
I'm so happy!

92
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:11,803
Souvenirs from Kumamoto?

93
00:06:11,804 --> 00:06:14,073
Yeah, I had some meetings
with Kumamoto Industries.

94
00:06:14,674 --> 00:06:15,841
Is it going well?

95
00:06:15,842 --> 00:06:20,379
Yeah. Soman was close to closing a deal,

96
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:23,182
but President Neo's negotiating skills
have us in the lead now.

97
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:26,985
<i>That's Kosei Neo for you.</i>

98
00:06:26,986 --> 00:06:30,555
Oh, yeah.
President Neo praised your foresight.

99
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:32,358
- Oh!
- He wants to meet you someday.

100
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:35,395
<i>What a sweet little sister.</i>

101
00:06:36,028 --> 00:06:38,498
<i>You can really feel
her love for her brother.</i>

102
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:44,003
<i>Reminds me of Eri's catchphrase
from when she was my secretary.</i>

103
00:06:45,004 --> 00:06:47,372
No matter how hard you push me,
if I think of it as coming

104
00:06:47,373 --> 00:06:50,376
from my big brother,
so it doesn't bother me at all.

105
00:06:51,511 --> 00:06:55,915
<i>If I hadn’t entered Eito’s body,
who should’ve died in the accident,</i>

106
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:59,552
<i>Eito would not exist right now.</i>

107
00:07:00,119 --> 00:07:04,757
<i>Her affection for Kosei Neo,
who resembles her brother, would grow--</i>

108
00:07:05,691 --> 00:07:07,192
You scared me. What happened?

109
00:07:07,193 --> 00:07:08,928
Oh, sorry. It's nothing.

110
00:07:10,163 --> 00:07:11,597
<i>How could I…</i>

111
00:07:12,899 --> 00:07:14,767
<i>I'd completely forgotten.</i>

112
00:07:16,202 --> 00:07:18,971
<i>When I was exhausted
from all the COVID countermeasures…</i>

113
00:07:19,472 --> 00:07:20,672
I drank too much.

114
00:07:20,673 --> 00:07:23,408
Good morning, sir.

115
00:07:23,409 --> 00:07:25,410
Breakfast is ready.

116
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:27,513
<i>Why is she in my room?</i>

117
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,449
<i>What happened last night?</i>

118
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:34,686
- <i>The questionable possibility…</i>
- Drink while it's hot.

119
00:07:34,687 --> 00:07:37,723
<i>…that I spent a forbidden night with her.</i>

120
00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:41,661
<i>If something like that were to happen
between Kosei Neo</i>

121
00:07:42,161 --> 00:07:45,231
<i>and Eito's little sister,
who is now my little sister…</i>

122
00:07:46,532 --> 00:07:48,634
<i>I'm not sure why, but it's complicated.</i>

123
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:51,870
<i>There's still time before COVID hits.</i>

124
00:07:51,871 --> 00:07:53,038
<i>In the meantime,</i>

125
00:07:53,039 --> 00:07:57,242
<i>I should steer Eri's heart
toward someone other than Kosei Neo.</i>

126
00:07:57,243 --> 00:07:59,579
- A bigger size…
- You can also buy it online.

127
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,648
Yes!

128
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:06,118
Sorry to call so late. It's Tomono.

129
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:08,754
Tomono!

130
00:08:09,455 --> 00:08:10,556
What is it?

131
00:08:11,057 --> 00:08:12,624
<i>Same as ever…</i>

132
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:14,861
<i>Such a sincere and kind young man.</i>

133
00:08:15,461 --> 00:08:16,829
I see. I will prioritize…

134
00:08:17,396 --> 00:08:20,032
<i>From the day we met,
he worked for the people,</i>

135
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:24,437
<i>and even as the company grew,
he kept championing welfare and relief.</i>

136
00:08:24,937 --> 00:08:25,837
<i>A "for the people"</i>

137
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:27,907
- <i>kind of man.</i>
- Thank you. Was it a long trip?

138
00:08:28,574 --> 00:08:29,574
<i>And…</i>

139
00:08:29,575 --> 00:08:30,942
Are you all right?

140
00:08:30,943 --> 00:08:34,547
<i>The man who took Eri to the hospital.</i>

141
00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:36,649
- Oh, no!
- <i>Tatsuki Tomono.</i>

142
00:08:38,718 --> 00:08:40,185
- <i>He's the one.</i>
- When do you need it?

143
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:41,820
By tomorrow…

144
00:08:41,821 --> 00:08:43,522
- Tomono.
- Yes?

145
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:47,026
Since you're here,
why don't you stay for dinner?

146
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:49,094
Oh, no…

147
00:08:49,095 --> 00:08:50,930
Let's eat together. Come in.

148
00:08:51,497 --> 00:08:52,632
- Come in.
- Come in.

149
00:08:53,432 --> 00:08:55,501
Thank you. Excuse me.

150
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,173
Delicious!

151
00:09:02,174 --> 00:09:03,942
Take some home with you.

152
00:09:03,943 --> 00:09:06,278
After all, you're Eri's savior.

153
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:10,349
That's so true.
Tomono is always helping me.

154
00:09:11,484 --> 00:09:12,884
<i>Good.</i>

155
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:15,421
<i>Eri clearly thinks very highly of him.</i>

156
00:09:15,922 --> 00:09:17,356
- You're welcome.
- <i>Oh?</i>

157
00:09:18,024 --> 00:09:20,258
<i>Tomono doesn't seem indifferent either.</i>

158
00:09:20,259 --> 00:09:21,760
The beef and potato stew is good.

159
00:09:21,761 --> 00:09:23,563
<i>Things are looking up.</i>

160
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:25,798
But it's strange.

161
00:09:26,966 --> 00:09:30,536
Whether at home or at work,
it feels like my brother is always around.

162
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:34,974
He really does look
remarkably like President Neo.

163
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:38,711
Well, I guess both of them are
pretty good-looking.

164
00:09:39,512 --> 00:09:43,349
Well, Mom was beautiful,

165
00:09:43,849 --> 00:09:46,018
so Eito must have inherited that.

166
00:09:48,321 --> 00:09:50,423
<i>That's when I noticed it
for the first time.</i>

167
00:09:51,657 --> 00:09:53,425
<i>Eito's mother</i>

168
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:56,195
<i>resembled my own mother.</i>

169
00:09:57,830 --> 00:10:02,068
<i>Come to think of it,
my father barely came home</i>

170
00:10:02,568 --> 00:10:05,237
<i>and gave my mother nothing but hardship.</i>

171
00:10:06,706 --> 00:10:07,839
<i>In the end,</i>

172
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:11,010
<i>she gave up on him and left the house.</i>

173
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:17,149
<i>At that time, I somehow found
myself accepting it.</i>

174
00:10:18,584 --> 00:10:20,418
<i>Because their mothers were similar,</i>

175
00:10:20,419 --> 00:10:23,656
<i>Eito Nomoto and Kosei Neo
ended up looking alike too.</i>

176
00:10:24,557 --> 00:10:28,226
Oh, right. There's some mail here for Dad.

177
00:10:28,227 --> 00:10:29,061
Huh?

178
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:32,164
Here.

179
00:10:33,165 --> 00:10:35,300
Tokyo District Court.

180
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:36,569
- Scissors.
- Okay.

181
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:46,879
Huh?

182
00:10:47,913 --> 00:10:51,516
Case for injunction and damages
for patent infringement.

183
00:10:51,517 --> 00:10:55,387
The plaintiff is Soman Co., Ltd.

184
00:10:55,388 --> 00:10:59,525
The defendant is
Akari Shopping Street Co., Ltd.

185
00:11:00,126 --> 00:11:02,561
and NEOXIS Co., Ltd.

186
00:11:12,304 --> 00:11:14,639
Patent infringement?!

187
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,107
Hey! What's going on here?

188
00:11:16,108 --> 00:11:20,111
According to the complaint,
Soman claims we took their climate goods

189
00:11:20,112 --> 00:11:22,580
and made and sold them without permission.

190
00:11:22,581 --> 00:11:23,481
- Huh?
- Huh?

191
00:11:23,482 --> 00:11:26,518
They're going after NEOXIS too,
just for selling them online?

192
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,987
Oh, no, it's my fault
that President Neo is caught up in this…

193
00:11:28,988 --> 00:11:31,022
But this doesn't make sense!

194
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:35,093
Wasn't that a product Eito came up with
and we developed together?!

195
00:11:35,094 --> 00:11:36,461
- Yeah!
- Right!

196
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:40,498
So Soman went and filed for a patent
and then sued us?

197
00:11:40,499 --> 00:11:42,300
Hey! Can we let them get away with this?

198
00:11:42,301 --> 00:11:44,803
- As President, I can't allow it.
- Right!

199
00:11:44,804 --> 00:11:48,239
Dad, I need to confirm something.
I think I mentioned it before,

200
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:50,376
but you did file
a patent application, right?

201
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:55,580
I sort of forgot.

202
00:11:55,581 --> 00:11:58,117
- What?
- Hey!

203
00:12:01,587 --> 00:12:05,591
Usually, a warning notice is sent
before a lawsuit, but…

204
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:07,459
I never received anything.

205
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,594
Nothing came to NEOXIS either.

206
00:12:09,595 --> 00:12:13,265
Suing without prior notice…
Soman is playing hardball.

207
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:18,604
If we lose this case,
could I, as President,

208
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:23,675
be sued for damages
or even thrown in prison?

209
00:12:23,676 --> 00:12:25,977
We're up against the mighty Soman!

210
00:12:25,978 --> 00:12:28,380
We don't stand much of a chance, do we?

211
00:12:29,148 --> 00:12:32,785
Don't worry.
I'll bring you care packages in prison.

212
00:12:33,285 --> 00:12:35,420
Though I might forget, sorry.

213
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:36,988
- You'll definitely forget.
- Yeah?

214
00:12:36,989 --> 00:12:38,991
I'll make sure it doesn't come to that.

215
00:12:39,558 --> 00:12:41,760
NEOXIS will respond swiftly as well.

216
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:42,961
SOMAN SUES AKARI SHOPPING STREET
AND NEOXIS FOR PATENT INFRINGEMENT

217
00:12:42,962 --> 00:12:43,862
NEOXIS CRITICIZED

218
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:44,697
Thank you very much.

219
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:50,436
Their filing date was
after our products went on sale.

220
00:12:52,037 --> 00:12:56,175
So Soman stole our idea
and filed the patent themselves?

221
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:59,945
And now they're going after us?
This is outrageous.

222
00:13:00,579 --> 00:13:03,515
If we can prove Akari Shopping Street
developed it first,

223
00:13:03,516 --> 00:13:05,351
we may be able to win this lawsuit.

224
00:13:06,051 --> 00:13:07,920
But something's odd.

225
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:10,455
Why would someone
of President Ichimanda's stature

226
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:13,292
file a lawsuit he could potentially lose?

227
00:13:14,193 --> 00:13:16,295
Maybe the trial itself doesn't matter,

228
00:13:17,062 --> 00:13:21,300
and the real goal is
to damage NEOXIS's reputation

229
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:25,471
and knock them out
of the semiconductor business.

230
00:13:29,275 --> 00:13:30,843
I'm amazed.

231
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:34,413
That's exactly the same conclusion
President Neo reached.

232
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:38,751
Sorry to take up your time, both of you.

233
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:41,787
Thank you for making time for me.

234
00:13:42,588 --> 00:13:43,489
Please, have a seat.

235
00:13:46,725 --> 00:13:49,295
So, what did you want to discuss?

236
00:13:50,229 --> 00:13:52,565
President Nagamine called.

237
00:13:53,065 --> 00:13:55,234
He's taking this matter very seriously

238
00:13:55,734 --> 00:13:58,971
and says a contract
with NEOXIS will be difficult.

239
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:07,813
NOTICE
CLIMATE GOODS ARE TEMPORARILY SUSPENDED

240
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:21,759
With this, we've gathered
most of the evidence to prove

241
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:22,694
Akari Shopping Street's innocence.

242
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:25,230
- Great!
- Yes!

243
00:14:25,231 --> 00:14:26,664
- Congrats!
- Yeah!

244
00:14:26,665 --> 00:14:28,867
Having NEOXIS with us

245
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:31,636
gives me great confidence as President.

246
00:14:31,637 --> 00:14:32,570
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

247
00:14:32,571 --> 00:14:35,140
Here's a token of our friendship.

248
00:14:38,477 --> 00:14:39,678
- Here you go!
- Oh!

249
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:41,313
- Hey!
- It's hot!

250
00:14:42,248 --> 00:14:43,448
- Good!
- Good?

251
00:14:43,449 --> 00:14:45,516
Is this the famous Akari croquette?

252
00:14:45,517 --> 00:14:47,652
Yeah.
This one's the minced meat croquette.

253
00:14:47,653 --> 00:14:49,554
- I see.
- Want a drink while you're at it?

254
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:51,957
- Yeah!
- Let's do it!

255
00:14:52,658 --> 00:14:54,459
<i>What a strange sight.</i>

256
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:55,460
- Here you go!
- Wow!

257
00:14:55,461 --> 00:14:57,763
<i>I never expected to see Tsuchiya
with a face like that.</i>

258
00:14:59,231 --> 00:15:01,065
<i>If this keeps up…</i>

259
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:02,200
- Okay!
- Beer!

260
00:15:02,201 --> 00:15:03,903
<i>maybe the eviction never happens?</i>

261
00:15:05,638 --> 00:15:06,537
NEW DEVELOPMENT
SOMAN VS AKARI SHOPPING STREET, NEOXIS

262
00:15:06,538 --> 00:15:09,540
<i>New developments
in the patent infringement case</i>

263
00:15:09,541 --> 00:15:13,411
<i>in which Soman sued
Akari Shopping Street and NEOXIS</i>

264
00:15:13,412 --> 00:15:14,813
<i>over climate goods.</i>

265
00:15:15,381 --> 00:15:18,283
<i>Soman filed and obtained the patent</i>

266
00:15:18,284 --> 00:15:21,920
<i>after the products were already on sale
at the Akari Shopping Street.</i>

267
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:23,055
Ignore it.

268
00:15:23,555 --> 00:15:26,225
Our company should stay the course.

269
00:15:27,693 --> 00:15:28,994
But…

270
00:15:29,561 --> 00:15:31,863
it's a losing argument.

271
00:15:31,864 --> 00:15:34,233
To protect Soman's image,

272
00:15:34,733 --> 00:15:39,504
it would be better to apologize
and drop the lawsuit.

273
00:15:39,505 --> 00:15:42,641
That can wait until after the deal
with Kumamoto Industries is done.

274
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:45,611
When the time comes, you will take…

275
00:15:46,979 --> 00:15:48,847
full responsibility for this.

276
00:15:50,182 --> 00:15:53,418
The coverage has softened
the backlash against us.

277
00:15:53,419 --> 00:15:56,387
I hope President Nagamine
changes his mind too.

278
00:15:56,388 --> 00:15:59,458
This is urgent! Watch the news!

279
00:16:00,926 --> 00:16:01,559
‎SEISMIC INTENSITY 7 EARTHQUAKE
‎IN KUMAMOTO PREFECTURE

280
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:05,029
<i>Repeating the breaking news.</i>

281
00:16:05,030 --> 00:16:08,567
<i>A seismic intensity 7 earthquake
has struck Kumamoto Prefecture.</i>

282
00:16:09,201 --> 00:16:11,402
<i>The magnitude was 6.4…</i>

283
00:16:11,403 --> 00:16:13,538
Let's move quickly to provide aid.

284
00:16:13,539 --> 00:16:14,439
Yes.

285
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,507
- Here is rice with chestnuts.
- Thank you.

286
00:16:16,508 --> 00:16:17,875
- Yes.
- Thank you.

287
00:16:17,876 --> 00:16:19,510
- That's good.
- Please eat…

288
00:16:19,511 --> 00:16:21,714
- Thank you.
- Yes.

289
00:16:22,214 --> 00:16:24,717
- Thank you.
- Here you go.

290
00:16:25,551 --> 00:16:26,785
One moment, please…

291
00:16:31,357 --> 00:16:36,295
As someone from the affected area,
I'm truly grateful for your support.

292
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:42,868
Right now, I am deeply eager to work
with NEOXIS once more.

293
00:16:44,036 --> 00:16:45,838
That is how I feel.

294
00:16:46,405 --> 00:16:50,241
Can I take that to mean the semiconductor
business deal is included?

295
00:16:50,242 --> 00:16:51,677
Of course.

296
00:16:52,211 --> 00:16:53,545
Thank you very much.

297
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:58,316
The condition President Nagamine
presented to us was

298
00:16:58,317 --> 00:17:02,888
that NEOXIS would need to outbid Soman?

299
00:17:04,256 --> 00:17:06,158
In the end, it always comes down to money.

300
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,696
Nagamine is quite greedy too.

301
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,302
This is the amount Soman has offered.

302
00:17:17,803 --> 00:17:19,037
OFFER AMOUNT: ¥20 BILLION

303
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,806
This amount is
simply too large for our company.

304
00:17:21,807 --> 00:17:24,309
This is when you go find
that money, Takarabe.

305
00:17:26,979 --> 00:17:28,347
I have a proposal.

306
00:17:30,182 --> 00:17:33,017
Depending on November's
US presidential election,

307
00:17:33,018 --> 00:17:36,321
there are clean energy stocks
that could multiply several times over.

308
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:38,357
You want us to gamble?

309
00:17:38,924 --> 00:17:41,827
It's not a gamble. It's an investment
based on solid intelligence.

310
00:17:42,327 --> 00:17:46,230
The think tank Alpha states
that Donald Trump has too many opponents,

311
00:17:46,231 --> 00:17:49,101
so Hillary Clinton will win,
just as the polls predict.

312
00:18:00,946 --> 00:18:02,448
I have a request.

313
00:18:03,482 --> 00:18:06,318
President Neo is asking a favor of me?

314
00:18:06,819 --> 00:18:10,789
He values your foresight
and is asking for your advice.

315
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:12,591
Advice?

316
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:16,194
If that advice leads to success,

317
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:21,200
he says he's prepared to hire you
under a high-paying employment contract.

318
00:18:22,468 --> 00:18:25,737
President Neo wants to hire me?

319
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:30,541
I'd like to see that too,
you and Neo working together.

320
00:18:30,542 --> 00:18:31,677
But…

321
00:18:32,644 --> 00:18:35,681
what does President Neo want from me?

322
00:18:37,416 --> 00:18:39,184
The US presidential election.

323
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:44,456
In your analysis,
who do you think will win,

324
00:18:45,157 --> 00:18:46,525
Hillary Clinton or Donald Trump?

325
00:18:49,027 --> 00:18:53,866
<i>This is probably an investment question,
where the company’s fate is at stake.</i>

326
00:18:54,666 --> 00:18:55,834
<i>Once again,</i>

327
00:18:56,535 --> 00:19:00,104
<i>it's something that never happened
when I was Kosei Neo.</i>

328
00:19:00,105 --> 00:19:03,976
I'm very interested in your view as well.

329
00:19:08,046 --> 00:19:09,515
I don't think America

330
00:19:10,916 --> 00:19:13,385
is ready to break
through the glass ceiling just yet.

331
00:19:16,889 --> 00:19:18,590
I'll take that as a reference.

332
00:19:22,594 --> 00:19:23,494
Wait.

333
00:19:23,495 --> 00:19:27,298
With Hillary’s environmental focus,
a win would further reduce fossil fuels.

334
00:19:27,299 --> 00:19:29,600
Putting everything into coal stocks

335
00:19:29,601 --> 00:19:31,169
is like throwing money away.

336
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,271
If Trump wins, everything flips.

337
00:19:33,272 --> 00:19:36,774
Every poll and outlet favor Hillary.
Betting on Trump is too risky.

338
00:19:36,775 --> 00:19:38,476
Do you want to destroy the company?

339
00:19:38,477 --> 00:19:41,413
Are you saying I'm wrong, Takarabe?

340
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:44,449
If you are, give me an alternate plan.

341
00:19:46,552 --> 00:19:47,686
Understood.

342
00:19:53,659 --> 00:19:55,194
May I ask you something?

343
00:19:56,728 --> 00:20:01,233
Why are you so determined
to stand up against Soman?

344
00:20:02,334 --> 00:20:03,802
Tomono,

345
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:08,006
have I ever told you about my father?

346
00:20:09,141 --> 00:20:11,842
Many times. You've already forgotten?

347
00:20:11,843 --> 00:20:15,514
No, it's just that I just reread

348
00:20:16,014 --> 00:20:19,050
my childhood diary the other day.

349
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:19,951
NEO TRADING

350
00:20:19,952 --> 00:20:22,587
<i>Would it sound childish</i>

351
00:20:22,588 --> 00:20:25,958
if I said Ichimanda was behind…

352
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:28,594
my father's bankruptcy?

353
00:20:37,603 --> 00:20:38,803
NOVEMBER 9TH, 2016

354
00:20:38,804 --> 00:20:43,274
<i>The ballots from the presidential election
in the US, held yesterday Japan time,</i>

355
00:20:43,275 --> 00:20:45,877
<i>are being counted across the states.
Results are expected shortly.</i>

356
00:20:46,445 --> 00:20:48,079
<i>Pre-election polls showed</i>

357
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:50,982
<i>Clinton in the lead,</i>

358
00:20:50,983 --> 00:20:55,587
<i>but Trump is outpacing projections.</i>

359
00:20:56,355 --> 00:21:00,259
<i>In the history I know,
Trump should've won.</i>

360
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:04,763
<i>But my presence has changed
things around me.</i>

361
00:21:07,499 --> 00:21:11,036
<i>In that case, election results…</i>

362
00:21:12,471 --> 00:21:16,340
<i>The latest results are coming in.
Major US media outlets are reporting</i>

363
00:21:16,341 --> 00:21:20,478
<i>that Republican Donald Trump
has secured the presidency.</i>

364
00:21:20,479 --> 00:21:23,714
- Yes! He really won!
- <i>Repeat…</i>

365
00:21:23,715 --> 00:21:26,217
I'm astounded.
Sir, you are truly remarkable.

366
00:21:26,218 --> 00:21:28,252
Now we can take on Ichimanda.

367
00:21:28,253 --> 00:21:29,154
<i>It has been reported…</i>

368
00:21:31,690 --> 00:21:35,360
<i>In the end,
American history didn't change.</i>

369
00:21:35,861 --> 00:21:39,698
<i>But Kosei Neo's history has changed.</i>

370
00:21:40,332 --> 00:21:44,970
<i>So has the history of
Akari Shopping Street, NEOXIS, and Soman.</i>

371
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:49,474
Sir.

372
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:57,683
President Nagamine
of Kumamoto Scientific Industries

373
00:21:58,250 --> 00:22:02,721
has informed us he's chosen NEOXIS
as their semiconductor partner.

374
00:22:07,726 --> 00:22:10,862
There's no way Soman would lose to NEOXIS.

375
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:16,301
It can't be!

376
00:22:17,202 --> 00:22:22,073
<i>Soman, which sued Akari Shopping Street
and NEOXIS for patent infringement,</i>

377
00:22:22,074 --> 00:22:24,508
<i>has announced
it is withdrawing its lawsuit.</i>

378
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:26,944
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

379
00:22:26,945 --> 00:22:28,679
- Right?
- Good!

380
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,880
- Right?
- Yeah!

381
00:22:29,881 --> 00:22:32,049
<i>We sincerely apologize for the tremendous</i>

382
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:34,051
<i>inconvenience caused</i>

383
00:22:34,052 --> 00:22:36,655
<i>by a factual error
made by one of our employees.</i>

384
00:22:37,155 --> 00:22:38,456
<i>We are truly sorry.</i>

385
00:22:38,457 --> 00:22:40,658
- Hey!
- What the heck!

386
00:22:40,659 --> 00:22:41,592
- Lower!
- Right!

387
00:22:41,593 --> 00:22:43,294
- Bow lower!
- Yeah!

388
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:46,997
<i>A comment from the president
of Akari Shopping Street has also come in.</i>

389
00:22:46,998 --> 00:22:49,533
- Here it is!
- Yeah!

390
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:50,468
‎AKARI SHOPPING STREET CO., LTD.
‎PRESIDENT EIJI NOMOTO

391
00:22:50,469 --> 00:22:53,538
<i>To be honest, I was anxious
about how much we could fight</i>

392
00:22:54,306 --> 00:22:57,274
<i>against such a massive corporation.</i>

393
00:22:57,275 --> 00:22:59,877
Doesn't Eiji seem like
a real president now?

394
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:01,178
- It's okay!
- Yeah!

395
00:23:01,179 --> 00:23:03,013
- It's okay!
- It's okay!

396
00:23:03,014 --> 00:23:05,150
<i>That justice has prevailed</i>

397
00:23:05,684 --> 00:23:08,719
<i>fills me with joy as President.</i>

398
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,421
Oh, right! Let's drink to celebrate!

399
00:23:10,422 --> 00:23:12,857
- Yeah!
- Okay!

400
00:23:12,858 --> 00:23:16,394
- Okay…
- <i>Thanks to them…</i>

401
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:17,562
Great news, Eito!

402
00:23:20,932 --> 00:23:22,967
Tomono was talking about you.

403
00:23:22,968 --> 00:23:24,603
He said you're amazing,

404
00:23:25,103 --> 00:23:27,939
like you can see everything coming.

405
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:32,911
How did you end up meeting with Tomono?

406
00:23:33,445 --> 00:23:36,915
He got me a PR job for an auto company.

407
00:23:38,183 --> 00:23:39,651
That's a big one.

408
00:23:40,886 --> 00:23:44,356
There's a shoot coming up.
Will you come, Eito?

409
00:23:44,856 --> 00:23:48,759
Of course. But Sarasa, you're amazing.

410
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,962
Your world keeps getting
bigger and bigger.

411
00:23:52,731 --> 00:23:56,802
But is this really what I want to do?

412
00:23:59,571 --> 00:24:04,009
I appreciate your wish
for me to succeed on a big stage,

413
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:06,178
but I've always…

414
00:24:07,379 --> 00:24:09,781
lived in a smaller world.

415
00:24:11,716 --> 00:24:13,084
A smaller world?

416
00:24:14,719 --> 00:24:17,522
There was a different kind of reward
that mattered more to me.

417
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:19,891
A reward?

418
00:24:21,259 --> 00:24:26,932
Ever since I was small,
I was happy when you praised my paintings.

419
00:24:27,766 --> 00:24:30,602
I painted because I wanted to hear

420
00:24:31,670 --> 00:24:33,004
your kind words.

421
00:24:36,174 --> 00:24:38,743
That makes me happy to hear, but…

422
00:24:40,078 --> 00:24:45,050
Even if there comes a time
when I can no longer speak to you,

423
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:48,320
I still want you to keep painting.

424
00:24:50,088 --> 00:24:52,557
Don't say things like that.

425
00:24:53,091 --> 00:24:56,394
You know…
You never know what life might bring.

426
00:24:57,596 --> 00:24:58,830
Really?

427
00:25:04,402 --> 00:25:08,974
<i>At that moment,
I couldn't take my eyes off her.</i>

428
00:25:11,476 --> 00:25:13,745
- Here she is!
- Shh!

429
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:25,856
She's like Ado Mizumori.

430
00:25:25,857 --> 00:25:26,924
Oh, Ado Mizumori!

431
00:25:26,925 --> 00:25:28,259
Who knows Ado Mizumori?

432
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:30,227
- Me!
- Me!

433
00:25:30,228 --> 00:25:32,196
- Shh!
- Shh!

434
00:25:32,197 --> 00:25:33,932
- Sorry!
- Sorry!

435
00:25:40,805 --> 00:25:43,808
<i>Once again,
I couldn't take my eyes off her.</i>

436
00:25:47,846 --> 00:25:49,247
<i>This feeling…</i>

437
00:25:50,582 --> 00:25:54,085
<i>is something I never felt
when I was Kosei Neo.</i>

438
00:26:00,559 --> 00:26:01,393
<i>Could it be…</i>

439
00:26:07,198 --> 00:26:08,400
<i>that I…</i>

440
00:26:11,102 --> 00:26:11,970
<i>am in love?</i>

441
00:26:21,846 --> 00:26:25,050
<i>But if that's the case…</i>

442
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:26,584
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

443
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:29,254
<i>…is this a love that can be allowed?</i>

444
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:42,800
Allowed. Not allowed.
Allowed. Not allowed.

445
00:26:42,801 --> 00:26:43,701
- A cut?
- No.

446
00:26:43,702 --> 00:26:47,472
Allowed. Not allowed. Allowed.

447
00:26:47,973 --> 00:26:49,407
Not allowed.

448
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:57,248
I guess it's not allowed…

449
00:26:57,749 --> 00:27:01,251
- What are you doing?
- A flower reading?

450
00:27:01,252 --> 00:27:04,288
- No.
- But you and Sarasa like each other,

451
00:27:04,289 --> 00:27:05,556
so there's no need to find out.

452
00:27:05,557 --> 00:27:08,525
Wait, have you fallen for someone else?

453
00:27:08,526 --> 00:27:09,560
No…

454
00:27:09,561 --> 00:27:11,062
Were you talking about forbidden love?

455
00:27:21,006 --> 00:27:21,840
Huh?

456
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:24,476
Huh?

457
00:27:26,044 --> 00:27:28,078
- You okay, Eito?
- Besides that, something happened.

458
00:27:28,079 --> 00:27:29,146
"Besides that"?

459
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:32,417
Cash registers are being robbed
all over the shopping street.

460
00:27:33,685 --> 00:27:38,490
Six shops were hit,
with losses totaling 93,000 yen.

461
00:27:40,025 --> 00:27:43,661
This could be the work of a ghost.

462
00:27:43,662 --> 00:27:48,566
In Building 4 of the Akari
Housing Complex, which is mostly vacant,

463
00:27:49,467 --> 00:27:52,903
a mysterious light has been flickering
late at night…

464
00:27:52,904 --> 00:27:57,075
There are rumors that a ghost lives there.

465
00:27:57,709 --> 00:27:59,411
‎-Scary!
‎-No way!

466
00:28:01,579 --> 00:28:03,014
- What?
- Hey!

467
00:28:08,753 --> 00:28:10,187
- Ghost!
- Huh?

468
00:28:10,188 --> 00:28:12,856
Sorry, the breaker tripped.

469
00:28:12,857 --> 00:28:13,891
- What?
- Huh?

470
00:28:13,892 --> 00:28:15,693
Tell us earlier!

471
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:17,861
- Wow!
- That was surprising!

472
00:28:17,862 --> 00:28:20,464
- Let's just calm down for a second.
- That was scary!

473
00:28:20,465 --> 00:28:22,900
A ghost probably wouldn't need money.

474
00:28:22,901 --> 00:28:24,301
- True.
- Yeah.

475
00:28:24,302 --> 00:28:25,804
- That was scary!
- Yeah.

476
00:28:26,404 --> 00:28:31,176
Right! Wasn't there a thief
like that back in the day?

477
00:28:32,877 --> 00:28:35,079
- You scared me.
- President Kazama!

478
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:36,513
- President Kazama?
- Yeah.

479
00:28:36,514 --> 00:28:38,682
Eito probably doesn't know about this,

480
00:28:38,683 --> 00:28:41,151
- but some 30-odd years ago…
- Yeah.

481
00:28:41,152 --> 00:28:43,620
…a company president named Kazama

482
00:28:43,621 --> 00:28:45,589
was a regular around the shopping street.

483
00:28:45,590 --> 00:28:49,259
He said he came to look after his mother,
who lived in the Akari Housing Complex,

484
00:28:49,260 --> 00:28:52,029
but he dressed in fancy suits

485
00:28:52,030 --> 00:28:53,831
and made big purchases by check.

486
00:28:53,832 --> 00:28:57,034
- Right.
- Honestly, I never liked him.

487
00:28:57,035 --> 00:28:59,937
But Hideko, you were head over heels
for him, right?

488
00:28:59,938 --> 00:29:01,271
- No!
- Come on!

489
00:29:01,272 --> 00:29:04,074
That designer watch of his
was so attractive…

490
00:29:04,075 --> 00:29:07,178
- Yeah!
- The checks bounced,

491
00:29:07,746 --> 00:29:10,314
- and his mother didn't live there either.
- Right.

492
00:29:10,315 --> 00:29:13,951
President Kazama vanished
along with the robbery incident.

493
00:29:13,952 --> 00:29:18,088
So he was a silver fox con man
posing as a company president?

494
00:29:18,089 --> 00:29:20,824
If he's still alive,
he'd be around 70 now.

495
00:29:20,825 --> 00:29:22,593
- Right.
- Yeah.

496
00:29:22,594 --> 00:29:23,495
You know…

497
00:29:24,028 --> 00:29:26,331
I spotted a suspicious old man recently.

498
00:29:26,898 --> 00:29:29,299
He had a scruffy beard,

499
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:32,337
but he was wearing a fancy suit.

500
00:29:33,605 --> 00:29:37,876
If that old man is the ghost…

501
00:29:40,812 --> 00:29:42,045
Let's find out!

502
00:29:42,046 --> 00:29:43,947
Let's go!

503
00:29:43,948 --> 00:29:45,048
A ghost or an old man!

504
00:29:45,049 --> 00:29:46,350
- Right?
- Yeah.

505
00:29:46,351 --> 00:29:47,451
- Surprise…
- No!

506
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:50,387
This is the infamous Building 4.

507
00:29:50,388 --> 00:29:53,056
It's basically a ruin.

508
00:29:53,057 --> 00:29:56,426
A homeless person
could easily be living here.

509
00:29:56,427 --> 00:29:58,796
- Hey!
- What?

510
00:29:58,797 --> 00:29:59,764
The light is flickering!

511
00:30:00,331 --> 00:30:03,802
The electricity should have been cut off!

512
00:30:05,503 --> 00:30:07,205
- Why are you laughing?
- Can we go in?

513
00:30:08,873 --> 00:30:09,840
This is scary!

514
00:30:09,841 --> 00:30:12,409
- Don't run away!
- I won't!

515
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:14,879
- Don't push--
- No!

516
00:30:18,016 --> 00:30:20,083
- Wait!
- Huh?

517
00:30:20,084 --> 00:30:23,221
- Third floor?
- One more floor to go.

518
00:30:25,190 --> 00:30:26,791
It opened!

519
00:30:28,159 --> 00:30:29,594
Yeah!

520
00:30:31,396 --> 00:30:32,764
- Hold on!
- Hold on!

521
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:37,100
Someone is definitely living here!

522
00:30:37,101 --> 00:30:38,403
- Huh?
- You're right!

523
00:30:39,404 --> 00:30:40,672
Akari minced meat croquette…

524
00:30:42,807 --> 00:30:45,610
Calm down!

525
00:30:47,278 --> 00:30:48,313
It stopped.

526
00:30:50,114 --> 00:30:51,215
- What?
- Wait.

527
00:30:51,216 --> 00:30:55,686
I'm gonna wet myself!
Where's the bathroom?

528
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:57,555
- Bathroom?
- Oh!

529
00:30:59,224 --> 00:31:00,758
Hold on!

530
00:31:06,831 --> 00:31:08,332
Hey, hold on!

531
00:31:08,333 --> 00:31:10,935
- Someone is in there!
- This is scary!

532
00:31:12,770 --> 00:31:15,006
Is anyone there?

533
00:31:21,579 --> 00:31:25,683
Could it be… President Kazama?

534
00:31:26,684 --> 00:31:29,787
Did… did you steal the money?

535
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:38,496
Please don't call the police.

536
00:31:39,497 --> 00:31:42,700
Well… That's easier said than done…

537
00:31:54,479 --> 00:31:58,082
Kosei? It's Kosei.

538
00:32:01,719 --> 00:32:05,723
I'm Taisei. Taisei Neo. I'm your father.

539
00:32:07,725 --> 00:32:11,229
<i>No way… A reunion with my father
in a place like this.</i>

540
00:32:14,699 --> 00:32:16,200
Did you forget?

541
00:32:17,068 --> 00:32:18,936
What are you talking about, old man?

542
00:32:18,937 --> 00:32:21,972
He's not Kosei. He's Eito Nomoto.

543
00:32:21,973 --> 00:32:24,776
And you're Kazama, aren't you?

544
00:32:25,276 --> 00:32:27,145
You are Kosei, aren't you?

545
00:32:29,347 --> 00:32:30,214
Um…

546
00:32:31,983 --> 00:32:35,720
This man might not be well.
I'm taking him to the hospital.

547
00:32:36,421 --> 00:32:39,324
- Eito!
- Are you okay?

548
00:32:53,938 --> 00:32:54,772
‎Come in.

549
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:20,865
If you'd like…

550
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:23,801
would you like to take a bath?

551
00:33:25,136 --> 00:33:26,237
Sorry.

552
00:33:36,481 --> 00:33:37,315
<i>I'm sorry, Kosei.</i>

553
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:42,053
<i>Your father's done in this world.</i>

554
00:33:43,087 --> 00:33:44,989
<i>I'm heading to the other world.</i>

555
00:33:51,129 --> 00:33:52,196
If you like…

556
00:33:54,032 --> 00:33:54,966
I'm sorry.

557
00:34:15,586 --> 00:34:18,022
<i>He was the father who abandoned me.</i>

558
00:34:18,589 --> 00:34:22,060
<i>Normally, I'd want to unleash
my resentment on him,</i>

559
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:26,062
<i>but right now, I am Eiji Nomoto's son,</i>

560
00:34:26,063 --> 00:34:29,367
<i>and I cannot act as Taisei Neo's son.</i>

561
00:34:41,746 --> 00:34:42,880
This person…

562
00:34:45,616 --> 00:34:49,887
She's my… Eito Nomoto's mother.

563
00:34:55,526 --> 00:34:58,029
Are you really not Kosei?

564
00:35:15,313 --> 00:35:18,116
Eito Nomoto…

565
00:35:19,851 --> 00:35:24,255
Do you understand that I'm not Kosei Neo?

566
00:35:28,192 --> 00:35:30,527
<i>Like me,</i>

567
00:35:30,528 --> 00:35:34,564
<i>is he unsettled because Eito's mother</i>

568
00:35:34,565 --> 00:35:36,100
<i>resembles his wife?</i>

569
00:35:38,569 --> 00:35:42,240
<i>Should I tell him?</i>

570
00:35:43,608 --> 00:35:49,113
<i>Should I let him reunite with his father,
something my past self never experienced?</i>

571
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:52,782
<i>Would the current Kosei Neo…</i>

572
00:35:52,783 --> 00:35:53,450
<i>ECONOMY COMPASS</i>
NEOXIS-KOSEI NEO

573
00:35:53,451 --> 00:35:56,220
<i>…even want to meet the father
who abandoned him?</i>

574
00:36:03,327 --> 00:36:07,064
The Kosei Neo you're referring to…

575
00:36:08,766 --> 00:36:10,468
might be this person.

576
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:22,246
Conditions for hospitalization
must be met first.

577
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:24,582
Please, come in.

578
00:36:26,484 --> 00:36:27,685
Excuse me.

579
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:32,023
There's a man here
claiming to be President Neo's father.

580
00:36:33,291 --> 00:36:36,727
- His name?
- He says he's Taisei Neo.

581
00:36:41,132 --> 00:36:42,567
Please have him escorted out.

582
00:36:43,334 --> 00:36:44,635
Understood.

583
00:36:48,206 --> 00:36:49,140
Kosei!

584
00:36:50,441 --> 00:36:53,044
Do you remember me? It's your father.

585
00:36:54,579 --> 00:36:57,247
Please, just hear me out.

586
00:36:57,248 --> 00:36:59,015
No, wait…

587
00:36:59,016 --> 00:36:59,917
Please.

588
00:37:02,620 --> 00:37:07,023
I'm truly sorry that
I left you behind when you were little.

589
00:37:07,024 --> 00:37:10,093
But back then, the company collapsed,

590
00:37:10,094 --> 00:37:12,095
and your mother left too. I had no choice.

591
00:37:12,096 --> 00:37:16,633
But even so,
you still achieved great success.

592
00:37:16,634 --> 00:37:19,403
As your father, I'm so proud of you.

593
00:37:21,205 --> 00:37:25,276
Please!
I'm being chased by debt collectors.

594
00:37:26,210 --> 00:37:27,445
Three million yen is enough.

595
00:37:28,179 --> 00:37:31,449
For someone like you now,
that's nothing, right? Please.

596
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:34,884
<i>How far would this father go…</i>

597
00:37:34,885 --> 00:37:35,753
Please!

598
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:39,055
You are not my father.

599
00:37:39,056 --> 00:37:42,993
If I were your son,
this is what I would say…

600
00:37:42,994 --> 00:37:47,230
"Get out of my world this instant."

601
00:37:47,231 --> 00:37:49,300
No, please… Please!

602
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:54,772
Please! Kosei!
Three million yen is enough!

603
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:57,407
Huh? Please! Kosei!

604
00:37:57,408 --> 00:38:02,046
Kosei, please! Hear me out! Hey! Please!

605
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:10,087
<i>That was the true Kosei Neo.</i>

606
00:38:11,622 --> 00:38:14,058
<i>What was I expecting?</i>

607
00:38:15,059 --> 00:38:17,428
<i>Spending time with the people
of the shopping street,</i>

608
00:38:17,928 --> 00:38:22,833
<i>without realizing it,
have I stopped being Kosei Neo?</i>

609
00:38:41,619 --> 00:38:42,553
Taisei.

610
00:38:50,528 --> 00:38:51,896
Are you hungry?

611
00:39:00,371 --> 00:39:02,506
I'm ashamed to still be alive.

612
00:39:03,808 --> 00:39:05,976
Here you go. Sorry for the wait!

613
00:39:06,610 --> 00:39:10,281
Oh! Hideko, Kayo! Welcome!

614
00:39:11,215 --> 00:39:16,386
CHINESE RESTAURANT

615
00:39:16,387 --> 00:39:19,889
Wait!

616
00:39:19,890 --> 00:39:21,024
- Well…
- Hey…

617
00:39:21,025 --> 00:39:24,160
His situation is so sad,
and he paid back the money,

618
00:39:24,161 --> 00:39:26,530
so I decided
not to turn him in to the police.

619
00:39:27,398 --> 00:39:28,899
- That's fine, right?
- Yeah.

620
00:39:29,834 --> 00:39:33,137
But you know… Even at his age,

621
00:39:34,038 --> 00:39:36,073
- he still has a certain charm.
- Yeah.

622
00:39:38,042 --> 00:39:42,380
Makes me think back… to that night.

623
00:39:44,081 --> 00:39:45,149
Hideko! Don't tell me…

624
00:39:47,785 --> 00:39:50,821
- It was only the one time.
- You did it one time?

625
00:39:51,589 --> 00:39:52,423
Huh?

626
00:39:53,224 --> 00:39:58,161
Oh, no. He wasn't after me.
He was after Haruka.

627
00:39:58,162 --> 00:40:01,297
Hey, listen! I saw it myself.

628
00:40:01,298 --> 00:40:01,998
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

629
00:40:01,999 --> 00:40:05,902
<i>The day Kinpei and Eiji
went on their hot spring trip.</i>

630
00:40:05,903 --> 00:40:08,805
<i>Haruka was all dressed up</i>

631
00:40:08,806 --> 00:40:11,241
<i>and let President Kazama in.</i>

632
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:14,043
That was not a one-time thing.

633
00:40:14,044 --> 00:40:16,279
Don't say that in front of Eito!

634
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,481
- Right?
- Oh.

635
00:40:18,883 --> 00:40:21,384
Actually, this is just my speculation.

636
00:40:21,385 --> 00:40:26,190
I didn't actually see anything.
Forget I said it!

637
00:40:30,027 --> 00:40:31,495
<i>If Taisei Neo</i>

638
00:40:32,096 --> 00:40:35,800
<i>was attracted to my mother's looks
and married her,</i>

639
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:40,905
<i>it wouldn't be strange
for him to also be drawn to Eito's mother.</i>

640
00:40:42,239 --> 00:40:47,445
<i>If that night occurred between Taisei
and Eito's mother some 30 years ago,</i>

641
00:40:49,747 --> 00:40:51,548
<i>that would actually explain</i>

642
00:40:51,549 --> 00:40:55,753
<i>why Kosei Neo and Eito Nomoto
look so alike.</i>

643
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:04,962
<i>In that case, the two of them…
are half-brothers.</i>

644
00:41:09,099 --> 00:41:11,634
Eiji! Are you okay?

645
00:41:11,635 --> 00:41:12,470
Oh! No!

646
00:41:12,970 --> 00:41:14,103
Were you listening?

647
00:41:14,104 --> 00:41:16,105
No, nothing… I just got here.

648
00:41:16,106 --> 00:41:17,907
- Were you?
- No, nothing.

649
00:41:17,908 --> 00:41:20,443
I didn't hear a single thing.

650
00:41:20,444 --> 00:41:23,547
- Oh, no!
- Hey!

651
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:29,086
- Please take care of President Kazama.
- Yeah.

652
00:41:30,988 --> 00:41:32,790
- Hey!
- Huh?

653
00:41:43,534 --> 00:41:46,804
Dad, are you all right?

654
00:41:53,944 --> 00:41:57,381
How did I look in that TV interview
as company president?

655
00:42:00,117 --> 00:42:01,252
You looked great.

656
00:42:05,289 --> 00:42:07,224
I wonder if Mom would have been happy.

657
00:42:08,225 --> 00:42:11,161
She always dreamed
of being a president's wife.

658
00:42:13,197 --> 00:42:14,765
<i>Could Eiji have already known</i>

659
00:42:15,666 --> 00:42:18,969
<i>about Haruka's feelings
for President Kazama,</i>

660
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:23,206
<i>and that's why he tried
to play the role of a cool president?</i>

661
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:25,075
That's what presidents do, right?

662
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:30,080
<i>If that's the case, how heartbreaking.</i>

663
00:42:33,017 --> 00:42:34,118
Mom…

664
00:42:36,053 --> 00:42:38,989
was the type of person
who would never betray anyone.

665
00:42:41,025 --> 00:42:44,495
So… nothing happened. I'm sure of it.

666
00:42:47,264 --> 00:42:48,098
Yeah.

667
00:42:49,867 --> 00:42:51,200
- Eito!
- Eito!

668
00:42:51,201 --> 00:42:52,602
- What's wrong?
- Eito!

669
00:42:52,603 --> 00:42:54,404
President Kazama has disappeared!

670
00:42:54,405 --> 00:42:55,572
Disappeared?

671
00:42:55,573 --> 00:42:59,910
He said he was going to buy cigarettes,
stepped out, and never came back.

672
00:43:00,744 --> 00:43:03,913
And all the cash from the register
is gone too!

673
00:43:03,914 --> 00:43:05,482
- Huh?
- Come quick!

674
00:43:06,050 --> 00:43:10,987
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

675
00:43:10,988 --> 00:43:12,957
<i>And so the mystery remained.</i>

676
00:43:13,757 --> 00:43:17,227
<i>Is Eito's father Taisei Neo</i>

677
00:43:18,529 --> 00:43:19,897
<i>or Eiji Nomoto?</i>

678
00:43:22,666 --> 00:43:23,566
JOINT DEVELOPMENT BETWEEN NEOXIS
AND KUMAMOTO SCIENTIFIC INDUSTRIES

679
00:43:23,567 --> 00:43:26,235
<i>Today, under the leadership of Kosei Neo,</i>

680
00:43:26,236 --> 00:43:29,939
<i>NEOXIS signed a contract
with Kumamoto Scientific Industries</i>

681
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:32,943
<i>to jointly advance
their semiconductor business.</i>

682
00:43:33,444 --> 00:43:37,747
<i>Through this, NEOXIS…</i>

683
00:43:37,748 --> 00:43:40,784
<i>Kumamoto Scientific Industries
semiconductor…</i>

684
00:43:52,596 --> 00:43:55,432
<i>By living as Eito Nomoto,</i>

685
00:43:56,133 --> 00:43:58,202
<i>Kosei Neo's history has changed,</i>

686
00:43:59,903 --> 00:44:02,906
<i>and the histories of those
around him are changing too.</i>

687
00:44:07,177 --> 00:44:11,215
<i>And for the people around Eito Nomoto,</i>

688
00:44:13,384 --> 00:44:16,754
<i>will their destinies change as well?</i>

689
00:44:18,989 --> 00:44:19,622
‎NEXT EPISODE
‎EITO IS SUBSTITUTING FOR NEO!?

690
00:44:19,623 --> 00:44:21,090
<i>‎How about use my brother
‎who looks like President Neo</i>

691
00:44:21,091 --> 00:44:23,593
‎to do the negotiation?

692
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:26,696
<i>‎For the three days until the president
‎returns to Japan, you're Kosei Neo.</i>

693
00:44:26,697 --> 00:44:28,531
<i>‎After all, I’m Kosei Neo.</i>

694
00:44:28,532 --> 00:44:32,635
<i>‎For some reason, I kept wishing
‎this moment would last forever.</i>

695
00:44:32,636 --> 00:44:34,003
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

696
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:34,905
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
